**Data and Parameter Collection**

The data for this study were sourced from the 2025 CHIK outbreak records released by the World Health Organization (WHO) [21] and relevant literature [22]. To conduct an in-depth analysis of transmission heterogeneity and intervention effectiveness across population groups, Foshan City was selected as the study site due to its experience with the largest local outbreak in Asia during 2025. As a typical area with active _Aedes_ mosquito populations, its vector ecology and climatic conditions are representative of southern China and even Southeast Asia. Moreover, the city's epidemic data are systematic and complete, effectively reflecting human infection patterns in a vector-borne transmission context.

